page.title: 04E.Horsley S. Flowers
page.content: The greatest find was the Greater Butterfly Orchid which is creamy- white and quite rare in S.E. Eng- land. We found bluebell and cowslip leaves, and carpets of Dog Mercury under the trees. List of flowers seen: Purple spotted orchid, Herb Robert, Buttercup, Self Heal, Wild Rose, Heath Bedstraw, Greater Butter- fly Orchid, White Bladder Campion, Dog Mercury, Common Agrimony, Purple Pyramidal Orchid, Deadly Nightshade, Common St. John's Wort, Harry St. John's Wort, Daisy, Thistle, Sorrel, Birds Foot Trefoil, Clover, Twayblade Orchid, Mint, Sweet Cicely, Yellow Hogweed, Wild Thyme, Potentilla, Chickweed, Forget-me-not, Black Bryony, Hog's Fennel, Salad Burnet, Heath Lobelia.
